<br>
It is in the human nature to classify.  It is a very useful tool and helps us to make quick decisions on little information that are MOSTLY correct.  And one of the easiest information to get about people around you is their look.  The color of a persons skin is a very easy way to classify people.  Any moron can see the difference between a white skinned person and a black skinned person.  So it is probably overused by morons.  <br>
<br>
However, there are certain physical characteristics that come along with race.  Take allok at asians.  THey are much smaller than other races.  Look how people with african ancestry dominate sports.  So is it unreasonable to think that mental characteristics aren't influenced by your genetics?<br>
<br>
But I think it is all a bunch of crap.  Perhaps you can find certain characteristics more often in a specific gene pool.  So what?  There is no survival need to make hasty decisions based on limited information.  Now there is plenty of time to make your decisions based on what you know of the human being and not what is prevelent in the gene pool.<br>
<br>
Sure I will try to avoid people that look dangerous.  If you dress like a gang member I will avoid you.  If you pierce your body multiple times in many different places I will avoid you.  I mean if you would do that to your own body what would you be willing to do to mine?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
So I will always make hasty decisions based on my visual impressions of a person.  But for me the color of the skin has little to do with it.  Mostly how they walk and dress and talk.  You can tell alot from the looks of a person.<br>
<br>
Are they well off?<br>
Are they athletic?<br>
Are they neat?<br>
What do they do for a living?<br>
Are they educated?<br>
What mood are they in?<br>
<br>
Most of these questions you can answer from just looking at a person with REASONABLE accuracy.  Sure you can be easily decieved but that is rare.  ANd the answers to these questions will change how most people will interact with that person.<br>
<br>
At one point you could answer some of these questions with reasonable accuracy by the race.  But as we know that was a self fulfilling discrimination.  The only way you could answer those questions with any accuracy was because people made decisions that perpetuated the conditions that kept people of a certain race that way.  Of course now how a person dresses is a much better indicator.<br>
<br>
At any rate we will always make decisions based on inadequate information.  That will never change. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uvenen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Venen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Whore</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/15/01 12:26:12 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.crocker.com/~denise/amflag.gif  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Are you proud to be an American?</span><hr size=1> IMO saying that all human races are perfectly equal is ignorant.  Every race has different attributes,  scientists can determine from the structure of the skeleton what race the skeleton is.  Skull sizes are different, the whole damn body is different.  This is not to say that idiots can run around saying oh my race is smarter than yours, obviously there are plenty of members of each race that are more intelligent or more athletic than some of the other race.  This still does not change the average intelligence or the actual physical makeup of other peoples of different races.  In the end we just need to accept our differences and get along. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showMessage?topicID=1335.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showMessage?topicID=1347.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.emailToFriend?topicID=1359.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feq